<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,762,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1302,1327]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[692,831,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis box="[692,831,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">H. aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of the male genitalia but differs in having stout microsetae on the pygofer lobe and a strongly dorsally directed aedeagal shaft produced into an apical sharp thin process rather than hooked at apex as in the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
